    "description": "\nConditions are favourable for the development of squalls with wind gusts up to 50 knots.\n\nA line of thunderstorms is expected to cross portions of Lake St. Clair and Lake Erie from west to east this evening.\n\n###\n\nPlease continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. For more information monitor Canadian Coast Guard radio or Weatheradio stations.\n",
    "instruction": "\nMariners are advised to prepare for potential squalls. Vulnerable vessels are most at risk and should seek safe harbour if underway.\n",
